criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  · CT-confirmed diagnosis of chronic Subdural Hematoma;

               -  Primary surgical treatment based on clinical symptoms (progressive neurological
                  deficits).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  · Significant contraindication to angiography (eg. allergy for contrast);

               -  Structural causes for subdural hemorrhage, e.g. arachnoid cysts, cortical
                  vascular malformations and a history of cranial surgery in the previous 365 days;

               -  Inability to obtain informed consent from the patient or legal representative
                  (when the patient has a depressed level of consciousness), including language
                  barrier;

               -  Monocular blindness on contralateral side of the hematoma;
